<img src="/mbimages/bstenderfoot.jpg" align="right"><span class="maintext">
<h1>Tenderfoot Class Scout</h1>
<ol type=1>
	<li>Explain the following: Scout Oath and Law, Scout Motto, Scout Slogan, Scout Sign, Scout Salute, Scout
		Handshake, and the Scout Badge.<p>
	<li>Attend regular religious services with the members of your family.<p>
	<li>Explain the symbolism of the Philippine Flag. Draw the Evolution of the Philippine Flag.<p>
	<li>Identify your boy and adult leaders in the Patrol and Troop and explain their duties and responsibilities.<p>
	<li>Earn the equivalent of one-half-day's wage.<p>
	<li>Tell rules at home that you need to know.<p>
	<li>Wash and darn your underwear and stockings.<p>
	<li>Plant and care for at least one tree.<p>
	<li>Enumerate personal health rules that you should observe. Plan a balanced diet for one week.<p>
	<li>Inspect your home for safety hazards and report to your Troop what you did to correct them.<p>
	<li>Demonstrate First Aid for the following: cuts and scratches, bruises, first degree burns and scalds, insect bites and
		stings, nose bleeding, pain, fainting, and headache. Demonstrate how to use the neckerchief as triangular 
		and a cravat bandage.<p>
	<li>Identify at least ten-(10) edible plants and demonstrate how at least three-(3) are prepared.<p>
	<li>Sharpen a knife or a bolo and use it in preparing firewood for cooking.<p>
	<li>Name the parts of a rope. Enumerate the characteristics of a good knot. Demonstrate how the following knots
		are used: overhand knot, fisherman's knot, figure-of-eight knot, square knot, sheet bend, bowline, 
		two-half hitches, timber hitch, and taut-line hitch. Demonstrate and explain why the ends of the rope
		must be whipped.<p>
	<li>Point to the four compass directions and show how to locate the North.<p>
	<li>Identify at least 15 out of 20 items in a Kim's Game.<p>
	<li>Demonstrate to a friend correct table manner.<p>
	<li>Be active in Patrol and Troop meetings and activities. Join a Patrol Good Turn for your institution or community,
		particularly tree planting and caring, and community  beautification. Give your Patrol name, call and yell.<p>
	<li>Discuss with your Troop Leader you commitments in the Troop and Patrol.<p>
	<li>Discuss how to guard against child abuse.<p>
</ol></span><p><div class="fb-comments" data-href="http://www.mbcenter.org/htm/ranks.php?rnk=bstenderfoot" data-width="540\: data-numposts="10"></div><p>&nbsp;</p><!-- InstanceEndEditable --></td>
              </tr>
